contents.desc: ƒÜevapi ‚Äì Bosnia and Herzegovina üáßüá¶ Around the World ‚Äì Episode 22
I‚Äôm attempting to cook a dish from EVERY single country in the world in alphabetical order. Today, we‚Äôre exploring Bosnia and Herzegovina!

Start by making the garlic water. Boil the garlic cloves in 200ml water for 5 minutes. Let it cool, strain out the garlic, and mix 3 tbsp of the garlic water into the minced beef. Add salt and black pepper, mixing well. Cover and refrigerate the meat for 4‚Äì6 hours, or overnight for best flavour. Once chilled, knead the mixture until sticky, shape into small sausages (7‚Äì8cm long), and refrigerate for 30 minutes.

Next, prepare the lepinja. Dissolve yeast and sugar in warm water, let sit for 10 minutes until frothy. In a large bowl, combine flour and salt. Gradually add the yeast mixture and olive oil. Knead for 10 minutes until smooth. Cover and let rise for 1 hour. Preheat the oven to 250¬∞C, and heat a baking tray inside. Once dough has risen, divide into 4‚Äì6 rounds (1cm thick), let rest for 10 minutes, then bake for 6‚Äì8 minutes until golden and puffed.

Grill the ƒáevapi on a high-heat BBQ for 6‚Äì8 minutes, turning every 2‚Äì3 minutes. You can grill the lepinja on the BBQ too, basting with juices from the ƒáevapi. If using a pan, brush the lepinja with juices and toast.
For the kajmak, mix with ¬Ω tsp salt and set aside. Slice open the warm lepinja and fill with hot ƒáevapi, a spoonful of kajmak, a dollop of ajvar, and a handful of chopped white onion. Enjoy!
